Selenium class 1

What is software testing?
-- identify the correctness and quality of the application

How many ways can we actually test?
--manual
--automation

When do we go for automation
--after manual testing is passed
--when environment is stable
--analyze our test suite and choose our automation tools
What automation tools do we know about?
--Selenium is the most popular,TestNG,Cucumber,Katalon Studio, UFT/QTP

Level of testing
--Unit testing
--Integration testing
--Acceptance testing
--System testing

Types of testing?
--Functional testing
performing to see the functionality of any app we are working on
--NON- Functional testing
  1) Performance testing
  2)Security Testing: we test how your system is behaving when someone try to hack your system

  What is selenium?
  --Is a set of tools which help us to automate web applications is manly use to perform functional testing

  Selenium components:
   1)Selenium -->Integrated development environment
   2)Selenium Grid -->Firefox plugin
   3)Selenium -->Webdriver
   4)Selenium RC --> Remote control
   What is Selenium Webdriver: It is an open source automation tool which allows us to perform actions on
   a web applications
   Webdriver is an Interface
   Advantages of Selenium webdriver:
   1)open source
   2)Works with different browsers and support cross browsing testing
   3)it works with different programming languages like Java, javaScript, Ruby, Phyton
   4)It is OS independent, you can work with ios, Windows and linux

   Disadvantages:
   1)Cannot test desktop applications
   2)No technical support
   3)No built in reports
   4)Cannot test captchas, images or videos
  get() vs navigate():
  navigate can go back and forward and refresh
  get() will wait for the page to fully load whereas navigate() will not
  get() will not keep th history of the browser whereas navigate() will

  close() vs quit():
  close() will close current tab
  quit() will close the whole browser

  fullscreen() vs maximize:
  maximize() will maximize the browser and you will still be able to see the control panel(back and forward
  fullscreen() will maximize the whole application
